text.tspan: (please complete before workshop)
Tue May 23, 18:00 Pacific Time
on Community Service Hour
This page and all links are available at https://phor.net/#nft-class
Buy a laptop computer (not a tablet/iPad, prefer Mac), and bring to class
Join Su Squares Discord, say hi in #nft-class
If you get stuck at any time, DuckDuckGo first, then ask in that Discord
Create a GitHub account, fill in ALL profile information, and a photo
Add your name here
https://github.com/su-squares/student-list/blob/master/
(edit that file, commit, create pull request)
Find and install a text editor like VS Code, make a "hello world" HTML file
Install Edge or Chrome browser, open that HTML file
Create a separate browser profile for playing with cryptocurrency
Do not access Facebook on this profile (if you already did just delete
profile and try again)
Get an obnoxious-color browser theme for that profile
Do not skip that last step
Install MetaMask extension in that profile (unnecessary for Brave)
Create four accounts in MetaMask
Switch MetaMask to Sepolia network
Find the Sepolia faucet; withdraw Ether ten times (so that's 10 Ether)
Send the Ether evenly between your accounts
You're done, bring your resume to class, engaged students get job offfers
